name: FDIC,  Quarterly statistic on the U. S banks in the lower 48 states, USA, 4th Qtr 2007
description:
The csv file has data more than 8500    banks in the U.S for which FIDC collects data on their finances, such as total assets, liabilities, deposits etc. 
Look for data on non-current loans (loans that are 30 to 60, 60 to 90, 90 to 120 or more days in default) and profits/loss as well percent of deposits that are insured by FDIC.
